heaviest_rainfall.status: The storm today is ranked 7th for the amount of rainfall recorded during one storm.  22.48mm fell at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour over 28.7 hours.  47.89mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 09 November 2025, marking an exceptional 144.8 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 34.3mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 28.7 hours; it delivered 22.48mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
